description:
Comment: 43 pages, 13 figures; new version written in terms of grids with free
  basepoints; added Section 2.12 on the link surgeries spectral sequence;
  various other minor changes

  A set of reals A={a_1,...,a_2} is called convex if a_{i+1} - a_i > a_i -
a_{i-1} for all i. We prove, in particular, that |A-A| \gg |A|^{8/5} \log{-2/5}
|A|.
